OVERVIEW
This project demonstrates the detection and investigation of Kerberos-based attack activity within an Active Directory environment using Microsoft Sentinel. The lab simulates credential abuse behavior associated with Kerberoasting techniques and implements detection logic using Kusto Query Language (KQL).

The objective of this project was to gain hands-on experience with:

Active Directory administration
Kerberos authentication logging
Detection engineering in Microsoft Sentinel
Incident investigation workflows
MITRE ATT&CK mapping

