🔧 Logging Configuration

Audit policies were enabled to capture Kerberos and authentication activity.

auditpol /set /category:"Account Logon" /success:enable /failure:enable
auditpol /set /category:"Logon/Logoff" /success:enable /failure:enable

Attack Simulation

klist purge

runas /user:user1 cmd
Inside the new command prompt session:

dir \\localhost\c$
This generated Kerberos service ticket requests associated with Event ID 4769.

DETECTION ENGINEERING
Microsoft Sentinel Detection Query

The following KQL query was used to identify Kerberos service ticket activity:

SecurityEvent
| where EventID == 4769
| summarize count() by Account, ServiceName, bin(TimeGenerated, 5m)

ANALYTICS RULE
A scheduled analytics rule was created in Microsoft Sentinel with the following configuration:

Setting	Value
Rule Name	Kerberos Ticket Detection
Severity	High
Frequency	Every 5 minutes
MITRE Technique	T1558

Investigation Workflow

Generated incidents were investigated in Microsoft Sentinel by reviewing:

Kerberos authentication events
User activity timelines
Service ticket request patterns

Investigation query:

SecurityEvent
| where Account == "user1"
| order by TimeGenerated desc
